    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.36.38"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">38</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">KLIK</hi> <hi rend="italics">Radio 950, Inc. 
                        <lb/>
                    Covering Missouri form the State Capital with</hi> 5000 <hi rend="italics">Watts</hi> 
                        <lb/>
                    <hi rend="caps">P.O. BOX 414 JEFFERSON CITY, MISSOURI</hi> 65101 <hi rend="italics">314 635-4136</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>March 27, 1972</dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Doctor John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>5835 Vine Street</addrLine> 
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska</addrLine> 
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Several weeks ago I wrote to you about the possibility of doing a radio program about the Missouri River sometime this Spring, after you return to Skyrim farm. I also mentioned the interest expressed by the high school church group my wife and I sponsor, at visiting with you about, or in, your rose garden about Black Elk and his religion. You suggested I write back sometime in the Spring, perhaps March.</p> 
                
                <p>It's March, and the trees here are trying to repeat rumors that it is also Spring.</p> 
                
                <p>I'm pleased that you wrote back to me last month, and I want you to know that I am still interested in both doing the program and bringing the young people to your farm. As I indicated earlier, both of these matters could be taken care of at your convenience. The church group would prefer making the short trip to Columbia on a Sunday afternoon. But the taping of the river program could be anytime.</p> 
                
                <p>Thank you for your cooperation. I look forward to our visits.</p> 
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>KLIK RADIO 950, Inc. 
                    <signed>Bob Priddy</signed>
                Bob Priddy,
                News Director 
                
                    <note>BP/jw</note> 
                
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
